<b>Ayra</b> - Lithe and quick as a fox,  she remains hidden among the dragons.<BR>
<b>Vizzini</b> - True strength of a champion comes from the mind, not the body.<BR>
<b>Meera</b> - Destroyer of minds and small planets</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uayraunderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ayra Underfoot</A> at: 1/31/02 12:24:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucaithcaidh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caith Caidh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 12:59:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1979.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!! blades or pierce? for Nightshade</span><hr size=1> I'm a level 35 Shade, specced in blades.  At this point, I strongly think that going blades is a BAD idea.  For one, I have done some tests, and using slower weapons does not seem to aid my PA bonus at all.  Also, weapon dps does not seem to have much effect on bonus for PA.  (I have a bunch of raw numbers that I posted on the vault boards which shows where I'm coming from here.  Didn't get a very large sample, but what I got concurs with my original impression)<br>
But the biggest factor is a comparison with another shade...<br>
I seem to be doing far less damage on my PA than Ciardha can do, when we compared last night.  My blades is over 2/3 spec, and my CS is one under full spec.  I haven't figured out the detailed cause of this, but it seems to be related to the decision to spec blades rather than pierce.<br>
I think the biggest problem with doing blades as a Nightshade is the naturally very low strength on both Nightshade races.  I gain absolutely no benefit, weapons wise, from my primary stat.  I have to say that if I could do it again, or if I was offered the opportunity to respec, I would go with piercers in a minute.  My highest PA (On a blue) topped at around 180.  Can anyone post comparative results from a piercer around 35? <p><IMG SRC="http://www.dopplex.net/sigfile2.jpg" ALT="Caith Caidh, 35th Season Nightshade, An Claidheamh Soluis" ALIGN="middle"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uasaphdiamondwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Asaph Diamondwolf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 10:33:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1979.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.greypathfinders.com/face_nime.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!! blades or pierce? for Nightshade</span><hr size=1> Sorry for the short comment, but with piercing, around 32, I've managed to pull a 200-250 against a yellow con. <p><IMG SRC="http://asaph.iwarp.com/images/sshot046.jpg"><BR>
