</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usunthasbayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sunthas Bayne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 1:58:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1979.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.webpak.net/~njb/emblemsm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!! blades or pierce? for Nightshade</span><hr size=1> I withdraw my statements on blades and delay differences. <br>
<br>
Please run your tests again post patch and see if your damage changes that much when you change from a blade to a piercer.<br>
<br>
I suspect only your base damage is changing, and so total damage shouldn't change all that much. <p><table style=filter:glow(color=#FFFFFF
strength=3>
<font size=1 color=#000000 face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>
 Sunthas Bayne<BR>Firbolg Hero<br>Guild Leader - Dei Gratia</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 10:34:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1979.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help!! blades or pierce? for Nightshade</span><hr size=1> No question pierce is the way to go.<br>
<br>
As a shade your str (used in blade dmg) is lower than (str+dex)/2 (used in pierce dmg) so given 2 equal stat weapons the pierce will do more damage over time than the blade.<br>
<br>
Look at the style lists, you will see a number of blade styles that rely on you blocking the target, etc that are useless to a shade.  Pierce has a great style list here that works nicely for shades.<br>
<br>
Comparing the weapons you will find blades are currently slightly better, however the recently found great left hand piercer is proof that that is being corrected.<br>
<br>
So really there's no reason to go blades and every reason to go pierce IMO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19>Main Hall</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
